  88,12,In it will be a running spring
  88,13,along with thrones raised high
  88,14,and cups set at hand
  88,15,and ňĻfineňļ cushions lined up
  88,16,and ňĻsplendidňļ carpets spread out
  88,17,Do they not ever reflect on camels‚ÄĒhow they were ňĻmasterfullyňļ created
  88,18,and the sky‚ÄĒhow it was raised ňĻhighňļ
  88,19,and the mountains‚ÄĒhow they were firmly set up
  88,20,and the earth‚ÄĒhow it was levelled out
  88,21,"So, ňĻcontinue toňļ remind ňĻall, O Prophetňļ, for your duty is only to remind"
  88,22,You are not ňĻthereňļ to compel them ňĻto believeňļ
  88,23,"But whoever turns away, persisting in disbelief"
  88,24,then Allah will inflict upon them the major punishment
  88,25,Surely to Us is their return
  88,26,then surely with Us is their reckoning